result.execSummary:
The defendant Dustin J.K. Viveros was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Child Abuse-Intentionally Cause Harm [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.03(2)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
Pay court costs.   **NOTE: THE DEFENDANT IS ORDERED TO PAY ALL COURT OBLIGATIONS TO THE CLERK OF COURTS OFFICE.   Payment is due within 30 days.  If the Defendant cannot make the payment, he/she must report to the Clerk of Courts Office to set up a payment plan.  Failure to comply will result in other collection methods including a civil Judgment and/or suspension of your drivers license for one (1) year.  This judgment may be collected by income assignment if you fail to pay fines and costs as ordered.
------------------------------

IT IS HEREBY ORDERED THAT the defendant's excess work release funds be applied to any & all outstanding Court obligations while serving his mandatory jail sentence.
------------------------------

No alcohol. No illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia. No contact with children under 18 (other than incidental) without approval by DHHS.
------------------------------
*AMENDMENT 11/15/2016 - CONTACT WITH MINORS AT THE PROBATION AGENT'S DISCRETION.
------------------------------

Counseling as recommended by Probation Agent.   Provide biological specimen to state crime lab for DNA analysis, and pay DNA analysis surcharge.
------------------------------

AODA assessment and follow through with recommendations.
------------------------------

02:37 PM  Court in session.  Case called.  Appearances given. 
ADA Matthew R. Leusink appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Defendant Dustin J.K. Viveros in court with Atty Larry R Pruden.  
Matter was on yesterday and was continued to today.  
Atty Pruden has had an opportunity to discuss things with his client.  
Probation Agent Tammala Wetley appears by phone.  
Theresa Anderson, Supervisor of Ms. Wetley is also present by phone.  
Tammala Wetley is sworn and testifies on direct exam of Atty Pruden.  
Court makes record that we are here for sentencing and not to revisit the revocation.  
Continued exam of Ms. Wetley by Atty Pruden.  
3:02 pm  Atty Leusink has no questions of Ms. Wetley.  
3:02 pm  Response by Agent Wetley to Court's questions.  
3:03 pm  Argument as to sentence by Atty Leusink.  
3:09 pm  Argument as to sentence by Atty Pruden.  
3:13 pm  Statement by Defendant.  
3:24 pm  Court makes record and sentences defendant.  

SENTENCE:  
Total length of sentence is Six (6) years; 
Three (3) years of IC followed by Three (3) years of ES;  
Concurrent with sentence now serving; 
571 days of sentence credit;  

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
1)  No drugs or drug paraphernalia.  
2)  No alcohol.  
3)  No contact with victim unless Agent consents and defendant's Mother consents.  
4)  Complete parenting classes.  
5)  AODA and follow through with recommendations.  
6)  No use of corporal punishment with his child nor with any child.  
7)  Pay court costs.  
8)  Maintain full time employment or education.  

3:37 pm  Court in recess.
